720457f-a.title: Manhattan: Hubert Street - Collister Street
720457f-a.text:
Hubert Street, north side, east from Collister to Hudson Streets, show-
ing a 3-story former stable of the American Express Co. The 6-story
structure on the right is No. 151 Hudson Street at the N.W. corner.
August 2, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

720456f-a.title: Manhattan: Hubert Street - Collister Street
720456f-a.text:
Hubert Street, south side, west from Collister and across Greenwich
Streets, ahowing the latter with the Ninth Ave. Elevated Line thereon.
No. 11-13 Pubert Street, the 6-story warehouse at the S.W. corner of
Collister Street (shown on left) will be demolished.
August 2, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
